&lt;/section&gt;&lt;h3 id="priority-axis-2-sustainable-economic-and-enterprise-activity-in-disadvantaged-communities"&gt;Priority Axis 2: sustainable economic and enterprise activity in disadvantaged communities&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The focus of Priority Axis 2 is to provide support and resources to localities with high levels of deprivation and low levels of economic activity in order to increase sustainable economic and enterprise activity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you are applying for funding under Priority Axis 2, please download and read the Priority Axis 2 Application Form, please refer to the National Guidance section to access the latest guidance and forms. The Application Form should only be completed by applicants that have been invited to do so.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Details on specific districts can be found below.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id="corby"&gt;Corby&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Corby has been allocated a budget of £2,418,000 &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; for a second phase up to 2014. The priorities for the borough identified in the Local Investment Plan (2011) are along the following strands: enterprise support, access to finance, access to resources and support, and reviving local infrastructure and environments. The latest call for activity closed on 28 September 2012 and further applications are not sought at this time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For more information please contact Jo Singleton by email &lt;a href="mailto:Joanne.singleton@corby.gov.uk"&gt;Joanne.singleton@corby.gov.uk&lt;/a&gt; or by telephone on 01536 464165.&lt;/p&gt;

