&lt;/section&gt;&lt;h2 id="applying-in-the-north-east"&gt;Applying in the North East&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3 id="application-process"&gt;Application process&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The process of applying for &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; funding is as follows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the local management committee issues ‘calls for proposals’ that set out the priorities for investment and the application process&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;outline applications are submitted against the criteria set out in the call.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;outline applications are considered by the &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; Team to assess eligibility and fit with the priorities of the Programme.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;outline applications are presented to the programme executive committee for endorsement.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;projects selected for inclusion in the programme are invited to submit a full application. N.B. this invitation to submit a full application does not guarantee that the project will be formally approved.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;projects that are not selected are provided with feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;full applications are independently appraised by the &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; Team.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;approved projects receive a formal funding agreement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Potential applicants are advised to:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;carefully consider the information within the relevant call documents and associated guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;consider national &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; documents available from the National Guidance section of this website that have been produced to support the development and management of &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; projects.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;consider local &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; guidance on the outputs and results projects must deliver, available from the Local Guidance section of this website&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Potential applicants must be eligible to apply for an &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; grant in accordance with Structural Funds regulations and comply with stringent EU regulatory requirements on:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;eligibility&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;match funding&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;record keeping&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;financial and output monitoring and reporting requirements&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;EU information and publicity requirements&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;tendering and procurement rules&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;state aid&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; funding is not available directly to individual Small and Medium Enterprises.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For more information contact the &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; Programme Delivery Team: North East on 0303 444 6475 or email &lt;a href="mailto:NE.ERDFenquiries@communities.gsi.gov.uk"&gt;NE.ERDFenquiries@communities.gsi.gov.uk&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id="calls-for-proposals-1"&gt;Calls for proposals&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are currently no calls for proposals open.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Details of any forthcoming calls will be publicised on the website and through regular Practitioner Network e-bulletins.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id="making-an-outline-application"&gt;Making an outline application&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;An outline application is the first stage of applying for &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; funding. Outline applications may only be submitted in response to a call for proposals.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The outline application asks for basic project details that will enable the local &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; Programme Delivery Team to assess the project against the project selection criteria set out in the relevant commissioning document and test its eligibility for &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; support.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Before completing an outline application form you should:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;read the accompanying guidance notes.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;carefully consider the information within the relevant call document.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;consider national &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; documents available from the National Guidance section of this website, that have been produced to support the development and management of &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; projects.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;consider local &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; guidance on the outputs and results projects must deliver, available from the Local Guidance section of this website&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Please note that applications will only be accepted if they are made using the outline application form and that all outline applications must include a completed financial annexe.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id="making-a-full-application"&gt;Making a full application&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please note the local &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; team will only accept full applications for projects that have been formally selected for inclusion in the Programme.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The full &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; application requires the provision of a significant level of detail. You will find it much easier to complete the full application if you are aware of the questions it asks during the project development process. As you will then be able to collect relevant information and evidence and begin to put in place appropriate project management systems.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Once a project has been selected for inclusion in the Programme you will be given a full application pack.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The time taken for a project to progress from the outline stage to full application and then through to approval varies significantly depending upon the size and nature of the project. Once a project is selected for inclusion in the Programme the local &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; team will agree a timetable for the submission and appraisal of your full application.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id="applying-for-funding-in-the-north-west"&gt;Applying for funding in the North West&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The North West delivery team allocates North West Operational Programme funding through a single appraisal process. In order for a project to be successful in applying for funding, the project must fulfill the criteria of the Investment Framework relevant to the type of project. There are 11 Investment Frameworks which cover 11 Action Areas over 4 Priority Areas. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id="how-to-apply-open-calls"&gt;How to apply: open calls&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Over the life of the North West Operational Programme, the North West European Programme Executive will formally call for project proposals to come forward. For each call, the Investment Frameworks will clearly set out the nature of the activity covered by the call, together with the required outcomes, outputs and impacts expected from investment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Potential applicants will be required to register their interest by approaching the Programme Delivery Team with their project idea. With support from the local  team, applicants with eligible proposals will then be invited to submit an outline application using the form available from the National Guidance section.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The outline application will be assessed against agreed project selection criteria which tests the project idea against the requirements of the appropriate Investment Framework.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Successful projects will proceed to the development of a full application. These will also be subject to an independent appraisal before any offer of &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; funding can be approved.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id="how-to-apply-non-competitive-selection"&gt;How to apply: non-competitive selection&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Local Management Committee, Regional Partners and the European Commission have agreed the use of non-competitive selection for a limited number of projects identified in the North West Operational Programme. These projects will be subject to full &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; assessment and appraisal before approval can be granted and need to contribute to: business support; regional productivity; and access to finance.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id="eligibility"&gt;Eligibility&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The local Programme Delivery Team makes decisions in respect of eligibility. It also advises applicants on the eligibility of projects, activities and costs as part of the project development process.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Eligibility for &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; funding will be tested against a number of criteria including the European Commission Regulations: No 1083/2006 and No 1080/2006, the investment priorities set out in the North West Operational Programme, the detailed specifications set out in the Investment Frameworks, &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; basic, core and appraisal criteria and the National Eligibility Rules.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Full details on sectors, activities and costs that are ineligible can be obtained from the local delivery team.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3 id="calls-for-projects"&gt;Calls for projects&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h4 id="priority-1-call-for-project-applications-proposing"&gt;Priority 1 Call for project applications proposing:&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1. Support for business incubator units (RONW only)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; Programme Delivery Team (PDT) and Partners have identified the need for the provision of new incubator space for high value for start-ups or for the enhancement of existing incubator services and as such both revenue and capital funding is available under this Call.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A budget of up to £10 million from Priority 1 (RONW) is available to invest in capital and revenue projects through this call.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The call is only seeking to support projects requesting a minimum of £1 million &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; funding.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Launched on Monday 12 November 2012.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Electronic Stage 1 signed application forms in PDF format with relevant annexes must be submitted by noon on Monday 10 December 2012 to &lt;a href="mailto:NW.ERDFEnquiries@communities.gsi.gov.uk"&gt;NW.ERDFEnquiries@communities.gsi.gov.uk&lt;/a&gt;. This includes a completed version of annexe 1 within the call specification document ‘Stage 1 Deliverability Test’.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For any further information about this call please contact &lt;a href="mailto:Norman.Williams@communities.gsi.gov.uk"&gt;Norman.Williams@communities.gsi.gov.uk&lt;/a&gt; (0303 444 6503). Alternatively use our general enquiry email address &lt;a href="mailto:NW.ERDFEnquiries@communities.gsi.gov.uk"&gt;NW.ERDFEnquiries@communities.gsi.gov.uk&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This call is for projects across the whole of the North West excluding Merseyside.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All applications should be submitted with relevant LEP endorsement confirming this is a priority project for the sub-region and meets the call criteria.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is therefore recommended that applicants contact the relevant LEP as early as possible (contact details for each LEP contained within the attached call specification). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2. Stimulating enterprise and supporting growth in target sectors and markets (Merseyside only)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; Programme Delivery Team and partners have identified the need for stimulating enterprise and supporting growth in target sectors and markets across Merseyside. This will be achieved through:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;developing high value / growth new enterprise:&lt;/strong&gt; supporting interventions to support innovative high-growth start-ups, including social enterprises, to establish and then grow&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;increasing sustainable consumption and production:&lt;/strong&gt; specifically through interventions that will help reduce the carbon and environmental impact of SMEs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Electronic Stage 1 signed application forms in PDF format with relevant annexes must be submitted &lt;strong&gt;by noon&lt;/strong&gt; on Friday 4 January 2013 to &lt;a href="mailto:NW.ERDFEnquiries@communities.gsi.gov.uk"&gt;NW.ERDFEnquiries@communities.gsi.gov.uk&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For further information about this call please contact Norman Williams (&lt;a href="mailto:Norman.Williams@Communities.gsi.gov.uk"&gt;Norman.Williams@communities.gsi.gov.uk&lt;/a&gt;) or Rachel Shwe (&lt;a href="mailto:Rachel.Shwe@communities.gsi.gov.uk"&gt;Rachel.Shwe@communities.gsi.gov.uk&lt;/a&gt; or on 0303 444 6503). Alternatively use our general enquiry email address &lt;a href="mailto:NW.ERDFEnquiries@communities.gsi.gov.uk"&gt;NW.ERDFEnquiries@communities.gsi.gov.uk&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All applications should be submitted with relevant LEP endorsement confirming this is a priority project for the sub-region and meets the call criteria.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is therefore recommended that applicants contact the relevant LEP and local technical assistance contact as early as possible (contact details contained within the attached call specification). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h4 id="priority-13-call-for-project-applications-proposing"&gt;Priority 1.3 Call for project applications proposing:&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Increasing SME’s Sustainable Consumption &amp;amp; Production and activity in the Low Carbon Environmental Goods and Services Sector (RONW only)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The North West &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; Programme is inviting project applications under Action Area 1.3 for proposals that provide support to Small and Medium Enterprises (SMEs) in the area of resource efficiency and the development of low carbon technology goods and services for the Rest of the North West.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The current budget allocation for the Call is up to £4 million for the rest of the North West. Low Carbon support for projects in Merseyside will form part of a future business support call for Merseyside only.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Launched on Monday 12 November 2012.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Electronic Stage 1 signed application forms in PDF format with relevant annexes must be submitted by noon on Wednesday 5 December 2012 to &lt;a href="mailto:NW.ERDFEnquiries@communities.gsi.gov.uk"&gt;NW.ERDFEnquiries@communities.gsi.gov.uk&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For any further information about this call please contact &lt;a href="mailto:mark.joslyn@communities.gsi.gov.uk"&gt;mark.joslyn@communities.gsi.gov.uk&lt;/a&gt; (0303 444 6491). Alternatively use our general enquiry email address &lt;a href="mailto:NW.ERDFEnquiries@communities.gsi.gov.uk"&gt;NW.ERDFEnquiries@communities.gsi.gov.uk&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h4 id="priority-4-call-for-project-applications-proposing"&gt;Priority 4 Call for project applications proposing:&lt;/h4&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Provision of Managed Workspaces (RONW only)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The North West &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; Programme is inviting project applications for proposals that provide managed workspace located in, or very near to, areas of particular regeneration need in the North West, where there are the most significant problems of worklessness.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While this priority is essentially aimed at the provision of ‘managed workspace’ it could support the provision business incubators. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A budget of up to £8 million from Priority 4 (RONW) is available to invest in capital ‘managed workspace’ projects.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The call is only seeking to support projects requesting a minimum of £500,000 &lt;abbr title="European Regional Development Fund"&gt;ERDF&lt;/abbr&gt; funding.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Electronic Stage 1 signed application forms in PDF format with relevant annexes must be submitted by noon on Friday 14 December 2012 to &lt;a href="mailto:NW.ERDFEnquiries@communities.gsi.gov.uk"&gt;NW.ERDFEnquiries@communities.gsi.gov.uk&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For any further information about this call please contact &lt;a href="mailto:norman.williams@communities.gsi.gov.uk"&gt;norman.williams@communities.gsi.gov.uk&lt;/a&gt; (0303 444 6491). Alternatively use our general enquiry email address &lt;a href="mailto:NW.ERDFEnquiries@communities.gsi.gov.uk"&gt;NW.ERDFEnquiries@communities.gsi.gov.uk&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All applications should be submitted with relevant LEP endorsement confirming this is a priority project for the sub-region and meets the call criteria.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is therefore recommended that applicants contact the relevant LEP as early as possible (contact details for each LEP contained within the attached call specification). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Outline Applications for all calls should be submitted on the Outline Application Form which is available to download. Guidance on completing this form is also available to download.&lt;/p&gt;

